Halfling Shaman<br>
<A HREF="http://www.whitewolfbrigade.com">White Wolf Brigade</A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usadara.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sadara</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 644<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/11/01 5:10:04 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Ragefire Reservation</span><hr size=1> Correct, if Naggy is up, Ragefire isn't.  The Cleric epic quest is such that you don't just kill Naggy if he happens to be up.  The Cleric has to be at a point in their quest that they have the pearl to turn into the Ragefire merchant.  Once the turn in is done, you kill the merchant and then the dragon you need to kill will spawn.<br>
<br>
So, cleric needs to have the turn in pearl first.  If the cleric has it and Ragefire is up at the end of your FG raid, then you are more than within your right to go for it and take him out.<br>
<br>
There is no reservation on Ragefire, he's FCFS.<br>
